##Shooting "sealed city diary" moved the whole net, b station UP main Lin Chen: WAITING FOR THIS CITY TO HEAL!

Micro-signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

I was hoping to find a different story on a personal level.

By Ying Chen

On January 29, the fifth day of the Lunar New Year, it was supposed to be an auspicious day for Chinese to burn incense and worship the god of wealth. In previous years, in the city of Guiyuan Temple, the crowds of people praying for blessings filled the city with incense and became one of the highlights of the New Year celebrations. Now everything is silent.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On that day, it was the seventh day after Wuhan was closed off. In the afternoon, Lin Chen drove out to shoot some video footage, and then went to the supermarket near his home to buy vegetables, and this was the second time he went out to buy vegetables after "closing the city. ".

That afternoon, Lin Chen received a text message from the traffic police in Wuhan, which regulates private cars, after which he may not be able to drive outside.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
30-year-old Lin Chen, is a B station's UP main, the screen name "Lin Chen classmate. ". Recently, he in B station personal account has pushed three epidemic situation in Wuhan Video, with the Camera Record Wuhan "closed city diary. ". To his surprise, the video was reposted by People's Daily, the global times and other media, and became a hit on the Internet.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
As of press time, in a single B station platform, three video broadcast volume has exceeded 20 million. In the message area, the reporter saw, reverberates most, is all over the country the people refuels for Wuhan the sound.

The "closing of the city" is an important node

As a Vlog-based UP main, in doing this pneumonia epidemic video, Lin Chen released most of the video life-oriented. Each time he planned a theme in advance and presented it as an event.

Lin Chen said that the first person to hear about pneumonia of unknown cause was probably before January 20, "first my friends told me that I had pneumonia, so I should pay attention to going out, and try to go to less crowded places. But the truth is, people didn't really care. After another two days, see is that more people say pneumonia, then I basically do not go to a crowded place, go out to eat is also eat to go, will also wear a mask.

But Lin Chen admitted that according to his observation, there were many middle-aged or old people who didn't care about this matter at that time, "Don't they think it's just pneumonia? Or is it because of limited access to information that they don't think it's something more serious? ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The next day, Jan. 21, Lin Chen felt as if things had gotten worse. On this day, he went out to buy some necessities as usual, and decided to record with the mobile phone lens in the new Crown Pneumonia, Wuhan People's real life, such as supermarkets, business circles, companies in the end what is the situation.

In the course of filming, he found that although there had been a lot of news on the Internet about the seriousness and urgency of the epidemic, about half of the people on the street were still not wearing masks, most of them middle-aged and elderly, but that day we young people have actually started to fight for masks, many places are sold out.

Lin Chen said he hopes to use the live-action video to remind people to be more vigilant and to remind those around them to wear masks. The next day, Lin Chen in B station personal account launched the Vlog, as of press time, the video has reached more than 9.5 million.

With the development of the epidemic situation, Lin Chen felt it was possible to make a special video for this epidemic situation, "before shooting the material is quite 'by the way' , but after shooting found that in fact can be more complete. So, there is a relatively high-profile Wuhan 'Fengcheng' that day video. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Yes, January 23, the 12th month of the 12th month, is a day that will go down in history for Wuhan: In response to the ravages of the COVID-19, on that day, wuhan's new pneumonia prevention and Control Headquarters issued a directive: The city's bus, subway, ferry, long-distance passenger transport suspended operations; no special reason, people do not leave Wuhan, the airport, railway station from the Han Channel temporarily closed. Since then, there are 11 million people in Wuhan into the "closed" time.

"The day the city was closed was a big time point for the outbreak, " Lin Chen told reporters. "under the premise of ensuring safety, he decided to take some more footage on the street. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
That morning, he and his girlfriend first went to the supermarket to buy vegetables, because just the night before he had a phone call with his parents and decided not to go back to his hometown for the New Year this year, "At that time, we heard that the food was sold out and we had to rush to get some back and stock it up. " Fortunately, the supermarket was well stocked, but there were a lot of people who felt the same way, and there was a long line to get in and out of the supermarket. But this time, says Lim, everyone was wearing masks.

And when Lin Chen again came to one of Wuhan's most prosperous places, he found two days ago there were three or three two people Han Street has been empty, shops all closed.

On January 24, the 30th day of the Lunar New Year, the 10-minute Vlog, which recorded life in Wuhan 24 hours after the city was sealed, went online. And all of the footage is available for the entire network.

"What can one do as a [ former ] media person and video creator living in Wuhan in the midst of an incident in which those who remain at their posts are struggling to keep the city running? I just want to try to do the right thing in my own way, just like thousands of people in Wuhan are doing."when asked by a reporter why he took the risk of taking to the streets of Wuhan to shoot the video, linchen gave the answer in a calm tone.

People want to know what's really going on in hospitals

This Vlog, not only let the whole nation see the epidemic under the Real Wuhan, also let Lin Chen in a few days received more than 100,000 fans.

Under the video, the reporter saw that most of the comments are saying "Wuhan refuels" . Others sent Lin private messages. Some said they needed help. Others said they were volunteers who could help. Still others left messages telling their stories.

"But the thing that many people are most concerned about is actually what is the situation of the hospital in Wuhan now? Because there are quite a lot of people talking about the situation of the hospital in Wuhan these days, which is particularly horrible, " Lin Chen said frankly, he didn't know what was going on, "because most of US locals are at home and don't go out for anything, we get the same information as you do, and no one tells us what's going on. But listen to close friends or close to the sick people, the hospital is now really a state of overcrowding, beds are very scarce. My own feeling is that if the symptoms are less severe, it's mostly me at home in isolation."

Then, Lin Chen can only go as far as possible to verify. He went to take aerial photos of a certain designated hospital, and at the same time contacted the local volunteers in Wuhan. In addition to asking them to provide first-line materials, he also asked the volunteers to tell what they had seen and heard in the first-line through interviews.

In addition, Lin Chen also collected some of the local situation of Wuhan People.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Drone footage

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On January 27, he put it all together and uploaded a third video. The video was created in collaboration with CCTV. "If you want to know this information, I will make this information out. This is such a simple idea. Although I can only orally restore it through front-line volunteers at present. " But to Lin Chen's frustration, while gaining attention, he has also been questioned by some, "It's really hard to do this as an individual. Some people say I'm a hot topic, others say I'm a victim of the national crisis, so I haven't decided what I'm going to do next. I want to be able to tell a different story on a personal level.".

However, it is worth emphasizing that in Lin Chen's view, in the course of the country's fight against the epidemic, various decisions have been implemented very quickly, including the decision to "seal off the city. " Although it was a matter of considerable seriousness or that the losses would be very large, it was soon put into effect, "I sometimes wonder if this had happened anywhere else, as we saw on the TV series, if there had been rumors for 30 days before the city was shut down, and then there had been some trouble from the citizens after the city was shut down. But the fact is, people in Wuhan basically have no complaints, we can not go out at home every day, and then the basic life can be guaranteed. It's just that the epidemic is a little bit more serious, but I believe it will pass.".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Indeed, as Lin Chen says in the film, supplies and rescue forces are arriving from all over the country. And he sees the people around him doing what they can, as if they were photographing Mount Vulcan, they were delivering supplies to the hospital, they were feeding the doctors, they were driving them to and from work..

Lin Chen said that although the virus has brought dark clouds to the city, people in this city are desperately trying to wash it and let it heal as soon as possible, "Even if the city is closed, PAP, I know we are not an island, because there are one billion people who care about you. Let us be together, and wait for the city to heal. And then, PAP, PAP, PAP, PAP, PAP, PAP! "

The epidemic situation in the surrounding cities also needs attention

Every day now, when I think about it, she calls her parents in Jingmen, Hubei Province. According to his understanding, family members in their hometown are also self-isolated at home at present. They can not leave the house if they can, "For example, my mother works in a prison. The prison where she works is now sealed. Then her unit will go to my door every day to call her twice, if the person is not in, the unit's measures is not in me to deduct your points, or give a record of what.

Lin Chen told reporters: "in fact, the surrounding cities in Hubei situation is quite serious. ". On the one hand, they have a lot of sick people, and then the hospital is really short of supplies. But people are paying more attention to Wuhan, and the surrounding cities are receiving less attention and less aid."

However, this situation has been concerned about the high degree of attention.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the evening of January 29, Hubei Province held a press conference on the prevention and control of COVID-19 infection, to update the province on the latest progress of the epidemic and Prevention and control work. Xiaodong Wang, the governor of Hubei Province, said at the news conference that medical supplies were in short supply, not only in Wuhan and surrounding cities but also in other parts of the province.

Asked how other cities in Hubei are strengthening prevention and control, Xiaodong Wang said that the top priority for city and state epidemic prevention and control is to strengthen the prevention and control of key areas and key personnel, now the situation in Huanggang, Xiaogan, Jingmen, Xianning and other places is quite serious, especially Huanggang, where there are more than 1,000 confirmed and suspected cases, "We must not let Huanggang become a second Wuhan. To this end, the province has decided to send a working group to Huanggang, other cities and states have also been stationed in the steering group, early detection, early diagnosis, early isolation, early treatment, in order to fight for the prevention and control of the epidemic initiative.".

Requisition order

Every man is responsible for the success or failure of the war.

If you are an ordinary citizen in an affected area, we want to show your optimism and listen to the help you need.
If you are a public servant or a donor of any kind, we would like to see your "most beautiful retrograde" and document your selflessness.
